@startuml Sequence_Diagram_Async_Transcription
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #444
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #888
skinparam sequenceParticipantBorderColor #555
skinparam noteBorderColor #AAAAAA
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FFFFF0

title ScribeHealth AI — Async Transcription + Retry Flow\n(FR-03, FR-04, FR-11, NFR-02, NFR-05)

actor "Doctor" as D
participant "Next.js\nFrontend\n(ScribeStore)" as FE
participant "MediaRecorder\n(Browser API)" as MR
participant "Supabase\nStorage" as S3
participant "POST /api/\ntranscribe" as API
participant "Transcription\nServiceFactory" as TSF
participant "Sarvam\nTranscriptionProvider" as STP
participant "Sarvam AI\nsaarika:v2.5" as SAR
database "Supabase\n(sessions)" as DB

== Recording Phase (FR-03) ==

D -> FE : Click "Start Recording"
FE -> FE : assertTransition(SCHEDULED → IN_PROGRESS)
FE -> DB : UPDATE sessions { status='IN_PROGRESS' }
FE -> MR : MediaRecorder.start()
activate MR
note right : Audio captured in browser\nWebM/Opus format

D -> FE : Click "Stop Recording"
FE -> MR : MediaRecorder.stop()
MR --> FE : Blob (audio/webm)
deactivate MR

FE -> FE : assertTransition(IN_PROGRESS → RECORDED)
FE -> S3 : Upload audio blob\n→ sessions/{id}/recording.webm
S3 --> FE : audioUrl
FE -> DB : UPDATE sessions {\n  status='RECORDED', audioUrl }

== Async Transcription Phase (FR-04, NFR-02, NFR-05) ==

note over FE, SAR
  Transcription is triggered server-side —
  UI is NOT blocked; doctor sees a spinner
  while the pipeline processes asynchronously
end note

FE -> API : POST /api/transcribe\n{ audioBuffer: Buffer, mimeType: 'audio/webm' }
activate API

API -> TSF : TranscriptionServiceFactory.create(\n  process.env.TRANSCRIPTION_PROVIDER ?? 'sarvam'\n)
activate TSF
TSF --> API : SarvamTranscriptionProvider
deactivate TSF

note right of TSF
  NFR-03: Factory Method
  Swap to Whisper / Google STT
  with 1 new class + 1 env var
end note

API -> API : withRetry(transcribe, maxAttempts=3,\n  backoff=[1000ms, 2000ms])
activate API #DDD

loop Attempt 1..3 (NFR-05 Reliability)
  API -> STP : provider.transcribe(audioBuffer, mimeType)
  activate STP
  STP -> SAR : POST https://api.sarvam.ai/speech-to-text\n  FormData { file, model: 'saarika:v2.5' }\n  Header: api-subscription-key
  activate SAR

  alt Success
    SAR --> STP : { transcript: "Patient reports..." }
    STP --> API : transcript : String
    deactivate SAR
    deactivate STP
    API -> API : break — success
  else Failure (network / 5xx)
    SAR --> STP : HTTP 5xx / timeout
    deactivate SAR
    STP --> API : throw Error("Sarvam transcription failed")
    deactivate STP
    API -> API : wait backoff(attempt)\nthen retry
    note right : Attempt 1 → wait 1s\nAttempt 2 → wait 2s\nAttempt 3 → throw
  end
end

deactivate API #DDD

API --> FE : { transcript: string }
deactivate API

FE -> FE : assertTransition(RECORDED → TRANSCRIBED)
FE -> DB : UPDATE sessions {\n  status='TRANSCRIBED',\n  transcription = transcript }
DB --> FE : OK

FE -> DB : INSERT audit_logs\n{ action: 'transcription_complete' }

note over FE
  Pipeline continues automatically:
  → Extract entities (Claude Haiku)
  → Generate SOAP note (Claude Sonnet)
  → Status → UNDER_REVIEW
end note

FE --> D : Transcript displayed\nPipeline advances to\nentity extraction

== Failure Path (NFR-05) ==

note over API, DB
  If all 3 attempts fail:
  - Session stays in RECORDED status
  - Error surfaced to UI
  - Transcript field left empty
  - Session can be manually retried
  - Audit log records failure
  No data loss — audioUrl preserved in Supabase Storage
end note

@enduml
